"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The heatmap function in seaborn expects a 2D dataset that can be coerced into an ndarray. The 'tips' DataFrame contains categorical columns ('sex', 'smoker', 'day', 'time') and numerical columns ('total_bill', 'tip', 'size'). The heatmap function cannot directly use the entire DataFrame as it is, since it requires a 2D array of numerical values. The code should specify which numerical data to visualize in the heatmap.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< g = sns.heatmap(tips, square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\\n---\\n> g = sns.heatmap(tips.corr(), square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\"\n}"